<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuerten Beats Kafelnikov to Reach French Open Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Gustavo Kuerten defeated
Russian Yevgeny Kafelnikov in five sets to reach the semi-finals
of the men's singles at the French Open here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten, the fifth seed, won the three-hour match 6-3, 3-6, 4-6,
6-4, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Kuerten, 23, the 1997 champion of the French Open after beating
Kafelnikov at the same stage, rallied from two sets and a break
down to book a semi-final.
</P>
<P>
He will next face the winner of an all-Spanish clash between
10th-seeded former finalist Alex Corretja and 16th seed Juan
Carlos Ferrero, who followed Kuerten and Kafelknikov onto Centre
Court.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Albert Costa of Spain downed ninth-seeded Australian
Lleyton Hewitt 6-3, 4-6, 6-2, 6-4 in three hours two minutes.
</P>
<P>
Costa next plays another unseeded Franco Squillari, who earlier
became the first Argentine to make a Grand Slam quarter-final in a
decade when he beat 15th-seeded Moroccan Younes El Aynaoui 6-4, 6-
1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Costa, a quarter-finalist in 1995, became the third Spaniard
into the last eight.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, world number one Martina Hingis blitzed
unseeded American Chanda Rubin 6-1, 6-3 as the Swiss teenager
moved closer to her dream of pocketing the only Grand Slam singles
title she has yet to win.
</P>
<P>
Also through to the last four is three-time champion Arantxa
Sanchez-Vicario of Spain, who beat fourth-seeded American Venus
Williams 6-0, 1-6, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
It is the 10th time Sanchez-Vicario, the eighth seed, has made
the last four of the event.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Monica Seles of the United States, who a three-time
winner here, was meeting Mary Pierce of France while Conchita
Martinez was facing fellow Spaniard and qualifier Marta Marrero in
the other women's quarters.
</P>
<P>
With Sanchez-Vicario next to face either Martinez or Marrero,
Spain is guaranteed a women's finalist. Hingis will play either
Seles or Pierce in her semi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
