<HEADLINE> Jordan, Vietnam for Closer Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Regent Faisal Bin Hussein
said on Wednesday that his kingdom is keen on strengthening
economic cooperation with Vietnam, particularly in the field of
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while holding talks with Vietnamese First
Deputy Prime Minister Nguyen Tan Dung, who arrived here earlier in
the day for a two-day official visit to Jordan, on enhancing
bilateral ties and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Nguyen Tan Dung conveyed Vietnamese leadership's compliments to
Jordanian King Abdullah Bin Hussein for his role as a major peace
broker in the Middle East, and wishes for prosperity of the
Jordanian people, Jordan's official news agency Petra reported.
</P>
<P>
Faisal, younger brother of King Abdullah who is in the U.S. on a
10-day visit, expressed Jordan's willingness to boost relations
with Vietnam, especially in economic spheres, Petra said.
</P>
<P>
The talks also touched upon the latest developments of the
Middle East peace process, and Nguyen Tan Dung expressed
appreciations for Jordan's efforts to work for a just, durable and
comprehensive peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
He also commended Jordan's accomplishments in introducing laws
and regulations to provide opportunities and appropriate climate
for foreign investments.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by Jordanian Deputy Prime Minister
Ayman Majali. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
