<DOCNO> XIE20000607.0011 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNICEF Calls for Drought Relief for Horn of Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Children'
s Fund (UNICEF) Wednesday urged international donors to support
the urgent appeal made on the same day by the world body for
drought relief in the Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
U.N. relief agencies and partners are seeking 378 million U.S.
dollars to address the immediate humanitarian needs of more than
13 million people affected by the drought, about 70 percent of
whom are women and children.
</P>
<P>
The appeal covers urgent needs in Ethiopia, Eritrea, Kenya,
Somalia and Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
The UNICEF portion of the appeal totals some 30 million U.S.
dollars and addresses needs in the areas of health, nutrition,
water and sanitation, education and services to meet the special
needs of children.
</P>
<P>
"We are already geared up and working full speed throughout
the region," said Carol Bellamy, executive director of UNICEF. "We
stand a good chance saving lives, but it will require sustained
action for several months. For that we need strong donor support --
and we need it now."
</P>
<P>
UNICEF has mounted nine separate relief flights into the Horn
since April, including four to Eritrea, and one each to Kenya and
Djibouti. Each flight carried up to 40 tons of relief supplies,
principally therapeutic milk and biscuits for malnourished
children, medical equipment, and water purification and storage
items. Two more relief flights are due to arrive in Eritrea next
week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000607.0012 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile's Foreign Debt Reaches 34.845 Billion U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Chile's foreign debt amounted to
34.845 billion dollars at the end of April, reported the central
bank of that country in an economic and financial report.
</P>
<P>
Of that total, 30.672 billion dollars correspond to medium and
long term debt, and 4.173 billion dollars were short term
indebtments.
</P>
<P>
The Chilean central bank said that the public sector's total
debt amounted to 5.804 billion dollars, while the private sector
owes 29.041 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Medium and long term foreign debt in the public sector was by
the aforementioned date 4.899 billion dollars, and the private
sector debt was 23.773 billion dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
