<HEADLINE> C.America Opens 22nd Security Commission Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The 22nd Meeting of the Central
American Security Commission was inaugurated Wednesday here by
Panamanian Acting Foreign Minister Harmodio Arias Cerjack.
</P>
<P>
The Panamanian acting foreign minister said during the
inauguration ceremony that the Manual for Regional Coordination
Before Disasters that establishes a mechanism of joint,
transparent, and participative action in case of natural disasters
in Central America will be approved during the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Arias Cerjack said that the isthmus countries will also analyze
the inclusion of the Mutual Legal Assistance Work in penal affairs
among Panama, Costa Rica, El Salvador, Honduras, Nicaragua, and
Guatemala, which constitutes instruments that will consolidate the
Central American integration.
</P>
<P>
He said that the analysis of the reasonable equilibrium of
military and public security forces, the annual program of
measures of promotion of confidence as consolidating norms of the
Central American integration will also be themes to be discussed
at the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The exchange of information on the efficacy of the juridical
instruments in the matter of democratic security, and the creation
of the Police Higher Studies Central American Institute stand out
among other themes.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala has proposed the creation and exchange of police
aggregates to the embassies, while Panama suggested the
establishment of a Central American Academy for the Prevention and
Reduction of Risks, Preparation for Disasters, and Environmental
Protection.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, to be ended Friday, will have two stages. The
first two days will be for technical meetings, and all the vice
ministers of the Central American region will take part on the
last day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
