<HEADLINE> Tourists Arrivals to Peru Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists arriving to
Peru increased 14.3 percent in the first five months of this year,
compared to the same period of last year, according to statistics
published Wednesday here.
</P>
<P>
The Industry, Tourism, Integration, and International
Commercial Negotiations Ministry informed that a total of 410,851
visitors from abroad entered the country between January and May.
</P>
<P>
The arrival of 359,518 tourists to this Andean country was
registered in that same period of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Peruvian government target for this year is to attract one
million tourists, after surpassing the goal of 900,000 foreseen
for the previous year.  
