<HEADLINE> Miss Greece Criticized for Contesting in Northern Cyprus </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus on Wednesday criticized as "
foolish" the participation of a Greek beauty queen in a contest in
northern Turkish Cypriot area of the island.
</P>
<P>
Government spokesman Michalis Papapetrou said in a statement
that "Miss Greece" Katerina Delli has violated the laws of the
Republic of Cyprus by entering the country illegally and recklessly
allowing the northern regime to exploit her presence there.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus has been divided into the Greek and Turkish Cypriot
communities since 1974 when Turkey invaded and occupied the
northern third of the island after a failed coup seeking union with
Athens.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Cypriots unilaterally declared a republic in the
north in 1983, which is only recognized by Turkey, against the
internationally acknowledged Republic of Cyprus dominated by the
Greek Cypriots.
</P>
<P>
Delli, during her contest in northern Cyprus, was featured in
the Turkish Cypriot press holding a flag of the northern regime.
</P>
<P>
Papapetrou said Delli's "presence in the illegal Turkish Cypriot
regime" to participate in the contest has provoked the feelings of
the Cypriot people.
</P>
<P>
According to the official Cyprus News Agency, Greek government
also criticized Delli's action.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Greek embassy here said that Delli's visit
to northern Cyprus is a private affair. "The Greek government had
no knowledge about the visit and consequently bears no
responsibility," he stressed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
