<HEADLINE> General Assembly Session on Women Negotiating on Final Document </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Two Working Groups of the Ad
Hoc Committee of the whole, which run parallel to the current
United Nations General Assembly's plenary session, are continuing
the negotiations on the outcome document of the special session on
women, Shirley Brownell, the spokesperson for the President of the
General Assembly said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The special session's final outcome document, titled "Further
actions and initiatives to implement the Beijing Declaration and
the Platform for Action, is expected to be adopted by the
governments at the conclusion of the special session on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesperson said Working Group I, which is responsible for
reaching consensus on the document's introduction and the chapters
on past achievements and current challenges, reached agreement
Tuesday on paragraph 31 of the document, dealing with science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Movement had been slower then the day before , but there was
progress, the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
There had also not been much movement in Working Group II,
which is charged with agreeing on the initiatives needed to
improve the Beijing Platform's implementation, Shirley said.
</P>
<P>
However, by Tuesday afternoon, delegations had reached
agreement on a further 12 paragraphs relating to the role of the
family, agreeing to retain 6 of 12 paragraphs and to delete the
remainder, Shirley said.
</P>
<P>
In the Contact group, whose task is to craft language on which
everyone could agree, agreement has been reached on paragraph 30,
dealing with globalization and the agreed target of 0.7 percent
Official Development Assistance, the spokesperson said.
</P>
<P>
Thursday, 5 P.M.is the deadline for the Ad Hoc Committee to
finish its work, and delegations are being urged to work
frantically to complete the document, Shirley added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
