<HEADLINE> Political Instability Leaves 300,000 Zimbabweans Jobless </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 300,000 Zimbabweans will
lose their jobs by the time when the country's parliamentary
elections are held on June 24 and 25 because of political
instability, the opposition Movement for Democratic Change said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The labor-backed party said in a statement that a sagging
economy, Afro- pessimism, land invasions, and growing violence in
rural areas would see the present level of joblessness rising, the
Zimbabwe News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Factories and other businesses, said the party, were closing
leaving at least 54,000 people jobless while 150,000 jobs in the
agricultural sector had already been lost because of political
instability. 
</P>
