June 25 in 15 constituencies of the South Nations, Nationalities
and Peoples Regional State.
</P>
<P>
The reelection is to be executed on the basis of a decision by
the board, which annulled of the May 14 general election in the
constituencies on verification of reports of irregularities.
</P>
<P>
The board said that voter registration would take place between
June 19 and 23, and election results would be announced in the
respective constituencies on June 27.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the NEB said that it could not announce the result
of the recent general election as scheduled because it has yet to
receive reports on results from some of the constituencies.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia held general elections on May 14, the second of its
kind since 1995. The result of the elections was originally due
to be announced on June 7. 
