the U.S. had agreed the pullout will cover 1 percent of the West
Bank.
</P>
<P>
Under the signed agreements between Israel and the Palestinians,
the final phase Israeli pullout should include all territories in
the West Bank, except Jerusalem, Jewish settlements in the West
Bank and Gaza Strip, and the military areas.
</P>
<P>
On the opening of a new residential area in a Jewish settlement
near the West Bank town of Ramallah, Erekat said Palestinian leader
Yasser Arafat handed U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright,
who visited Ramallah Tuesday, a detailed list of the settlement
areas which have recently been approved by the Israeli cabinet for
building new residential units.
</P>
<P>
While terming the settlement activity as destructive to the
peace process, Erekat demanded immediate U.S. interference in the
matter.
</P>
<P>
He also echoed accusations by the Palestinian leadership that
Barak and his government should be held responsible for the
deteriorating situation in the peace process and the current
deadlock in the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations. 
</P>
