Culture Minister U Win Sein, Deputy Culture Minister U Soe Nyunt
and other government officials as well as foreign diplomats,
Myanmar-Chinese and others, totaling more than 1,500.
</P>
<P>
Before the performance in Yangon, the Chinese Guangxi acrobatic
troupe had staged three shows in Mandalay, Myanmar's second
largest city.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese acrobatic troupe's performance in Myanmar
constitutes China's part of a series of activities in celebration
of the 50th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The troupe will give three performances in Yangon. 
