<HEADLINE> Navratilova, de Swardt Out of French Open Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Martina Navratilova's comeback in
doubles came to an end here on Wednesday when the all-time great
and her doubles partner Mariaan de Swardt lost their third round
match in the French Open women's doubles.
</P>
<P>
Sixth-seeded pair Alexandra Fusai and Nathalie Tauziat of
France beat Navrtilova and de Swardt 2-6, 6-2, 7-5 to advance to
the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Navratilova, 43, has linked with South African de Swardt to
play doubles at four events this summer - culminating with
Wimbledon later this month, where Navratilova could win a record
20th title.
</P>
<P>
Navratilova won 167 singles titles during her remarkable
career. Along with her 18 Grand Slam singles crowns she also
collected 31 Grand Slam women's doubles and seven mixed doubles
titles along the way. But she has not played singles
competitively since 1994. 
