<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HKEx in Discussion of Global Equity Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Exchanges and Clearing
Ltd (HKEx) announced Wednesday that it is participating in
discussions with seven other bourses to explore the feasibility of
a Global Equity Market.
</P>
<P>
The discussion is aimed to inter-connect participant exchanges'
trading systems and to develop a market structure based on the
principles of transparency, self-regulation and agency auction
price discovery.
</P>
<P>
The seven bourses -- The New York Stock Exchange (NYSE), the
Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Australian Stock Exchange, Euronext, the
Toronto Stock Exchange, the Bolsa Mexicana de Valores and the
Bolsa de Valores de Sao Paulo -- cover the three main time zones
of Asia-Pacific, Europe and the Americas.
</P>
<P>
The market capitalization of the companies listed on these
exchanges exceeds 20 trillion U.S. dollars, of which the NYSE's
listed companies represent approximately half.
</P>
<P>
The Global Equity Market will seek to provide investors around
the world with a transparent, round-the-clock, trading mechanism
for the world's global companies, increasing the global liquidity
of their stocks as well as aiding global price discovery, said the
announcement of the HKEx.
</P>
<P>
Investor will be able to access the Global Equity Market
through their domestic stock exchanges, which will keep their
brands and individual standing while participating in a virtual
global pool of liquidity.
</P>
<P>
Participation in the Global Equity Market is open to all stock
exchanges that adhere to the principles of transparency, self-
regulation and the agency auction structure, according to the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The Global Equity Market will pursue opportunities and
economies of scale that will lower transaction costs for investors
and intermediaries.
</P>
<P>
HKEx Chairman Charles Lee said Hong Kong is committed to the
concept of a 24-hour global market linking the three main time
zones and is in close cooperation with international exchanges to
achieve this. 
</P>
</TEXT>
