<BODY>
<HEADLINE> General Assembly Session on Women Makes Headway on Final Document </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 7 (Xinhua -- The United Nations General
Assembly on Wednesday entered the third day of its special session
to review the progress of women's rights, making headway in
approving the document that will pave the way for further
implementation of the Platform for Action approved five years ago
at the Fourth World Conference on Women in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
According to a U.N. official, meanwhile, the session's final
outcome document, titled "Further actions and initiatives to
implement the Beijing Declaration and the Platform for Action", is
the subject of intensive informal consultations in two Working
Groups of the Ad Hoc of Committee of the Whole, which runs
parallel to the Assembly's plenary session.
</P>
<P>
The Groups are mandated with reaching consensus on the final
declaration to be adopted on June 9, the last day of the special
session.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. official said the consultations in Working Group I,
which is responsible for reaching consensus on the document's
introduction and the chapters on past achievements and current
challenges, had not succeeded in clearing entire paragraphs.
</P>
<P>
Group II, which is charged with agreeing on the initiatives
needed to improve the Platform's implementation, was able to
approve 23 paragraphs, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Working Group I had problems with certain paragraphs on family,
health and armed conflict, and forwarded the contentious sections
to a "Contact group" whose task was to craft language on which
everyone could agree, the official added.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations General Assembly special session on women,
under the theme of "Women 2000: Gender Equality, Development and
Peace for the Twenty-first Century," is focusing on examples of
good practices, positive actions, lessons learned, obstacles and
key challenges remaining in implementing the Beijing Platform for
Action in the last five years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
