<HEADLINE> 660 Candidates to Run For Election In Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Some 660 candidates were
registered to run for the upcoming election of the State Great
Khural (parliament) scheduled for July 2, said the Mongolian
General Election Committee Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the candidates are Mongolian Prime Minister
Rinchinnyamiin Amarjaragal, three former premiers and more than 50
parliamentary members, who will compete for the 76 seats in the
parliament.
</P>
<P>
The committee said in some constituencies, more than 10
candidates are expected to run for one parliamentary seat.
</P>
<P>
A total of 13 Mongolian political parties and three coalitions,
including the Mongolian People's Revolutionary party (MPRP), the
Mongolian Social Democratic Party (MSDP) and the Democratic Union
Coalition, will contest in the election, from which the MPRP is
likely to emerge as the winner, according to the latest poll, .
</P>
<P>
In 1996, 302 candidates from five parties and two coalitions
participated in the parliamentary election. 
</P>
