<DOCNO> XIE20000607.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ma's Army Win 5,000m, Fail in 800m </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dong Yanmei, 10,000m champion in the 1997 National Games, won
the 5,000m title with a time of 15 minutes 3.99 seconds, a far cry
from her training partner Jiang Bo's world record of 14:28.09, set
in the same National Games.
</P>
<P>
Yin Lili finished second in 15:06.30, Song Liqing third in 15:
18.62 and Lan Lixin fourth in 15:32.84.
</P>
<P>
This was the first overall victory for Ma's Family Army since
his students claimed three gold medals and two world records in
the National Games three years ago in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
But Ma's runners suffered a surprise defeat in the 800m event
as Lin Na was overtaken just a few meters from the finish line
after leading most of the race.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yuanping, who was not from Ma's training camp, took the
victory in two minutes 0.63 seconds. Lin finished second with 0.
04 seconds behind. Ma's another runner Yang Wei came in third
with a time of 2:02.82.
</P>
<P>
It was later found that one of Lin's feet was injured by a nail
in the shoe. "How could she perform well with such an injury?" Ma
said after the race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
