<DOCNO> XIE20000607.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yunnan Cooperates with Sichuan in Western China Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Yunnan and
Sichuan provinces signed an agreement on boosting regional
economic cooperation here today.
</P>
<P>
To improve their transport facilities, the two provinces will
jointly build the highway section linking Chengdu-Yibin-Kunming on
the No. 108 national trunk and the Chengdu-Panzhihua-Kunming
section on national road No. 213.
</P>
<P>
The two provinces will work together to open a number of new
tourist routes including those to Xichang, a satellite launching
center, and Lijiang, a historical city.
</P>
<P>
As the two provinces are rich in herbal medicine resources,
they will join hands to develop traditional medicine using modern
technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
