<HEADLINE> China to Hold Nationwide E-Business Test </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The China Internet Network
Information Center today announced it will hold a nationwide E-
business test on an annual basis in a bid to promote E-business in
the country.
</P>
<P>
The center will cooperate with the China Enterprise Net (www.ce.
net.cn) in providing training programs for people who are to
participate in the test.
</P>
<P>
The center said at a press conference here today that those who
pass the test will be given a certificate, which will be regarded
as qualification for engaging in E-business operations.
</P>
<P>
The training will begin in two months, but the exact date for
the first test is not yet decided, the center said.
</P>
<P>
The center is a non-profit institution authorized by the
government to manage Internet-related business and provide related
services, including domain name registration. 
</P>
</TEXT>
