<HEADLINE> China's Fujian Province Seeks High Tech Cooperation in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- More than 350 business leaders
from Southeast China's Fujian Province and Hong Kong gathered here
Wednesday for a presentation to seek further cooperation in new
and high technology industries.
</P>
<P>
"High tech industries in Fujian have entered a new phase of
development, providing ample space and opportunity for investment,
" Xi Jinping, governor of Fujian, said at the gathering.
</P>
<P>
The prospect looks brighter for a joint effort to speed up the
development of high tech industries in Fujjian, and Hong Kong has
become a key export destination and external capital source for
the province, Xi explained.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the governor said, Fujian planned a number of
steps to expand cooperation in science and technology between
Fujian and Hong Kong, including establishing a risk investment
mechanism and encouraging people from Hong Kong's business and
science circles to involve in research and development projects of
Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Other major steps include attracting Hong Kong high technology
businesses to operate in Fujian, raising funds in Hong Kong's
capital market for Fujian's enterprises, and building a joint high-
tech industrial park in Fujian, according to Xi.
</P>
<P>
Fujian had 26,281 foreign invested enterprises by the end of
1999, involving a contractual investment of 59.58 billion U.S.
dollars, which put the province in the third place in the country
in terms of foreign investment, and the total foreign trade volume
hit 17.645 billion U.S. dollars in 1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
