<HEADLINE> Thousands of Chinese Ph.D. Candidates to Help in Countryside </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Some 2,000 Ph.D. candidates are
scheduled to work in China's countryside during their summer
vacation to assist with local economic development.
</P>
<P>
The program, jointly sponsored by the Central Committee of
Communist Youth League of China and the All-China Students'
Federation, will assign doctoral students to help out with more
than 400 badly-needed projects submitted by local governments.
</P>
<P>
Leading schools such as the universities of Beijing, Nanjing
and Jilin have shown great interest in the program, and have
assigned groups of Ph.D. candidates majoring in certain fields to
appropriate projects.
</P>
<P>
"China has some 40,000 Ph.D. candidates and five percent of
them have volunteered to work for rural areas. I'm sure their
special fields of study will help promote local economic
development," said an official with the Central Committee of the
Communist Youth League.
</P>
<P>
The volunteers will maintain communication with the local
governments after the two-month summer vocation is finished, and
they may also bring the projects that are not accomplished back to
schools for continued research, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
