<HEADLINE> China, Moldova Issue Joint Statement (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Moldova reiterates that there is only one China in the world,
the Government of the People's Republic of China is the sole
legitimate government of China, and Taiwan is an inalienable part
of China. Moldova supports China to realize its grand cause of
national reunification at an earlier date.
</P>
<P>
The Moldova Government also reiterates that it will not
establish official ties or contacts with Taiwan in any form, and
nor will it support Taiwan to join any international organization
that is eligible only for sovereign countries.
</P>
<P>
The two sides denounce separatism, and support countries in
their efforts to fight such activities that are harmful to
national sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agree that their governments should encourage
their various departments and localities to establish direct links,
so as to further bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will, under the basis of equality and mutual
benefit, take measures to promote cooperation in areas including
politics, legislation, science and technology, agriculture,
education, culture, public heath and the press.
</P>
</TEXT>
