<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Close Slightly Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks edged up 38.38
points, or 0.24 percent, to close at 15,900.06 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Driving the market up was banking giant HSBC Holdings, analysts
said. The stock gained 3.07 percent to 97.25 HK dollars as
investors focused on banking counters amid easing interests rates
rise fears.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng Bank surged 3.6 percent to 72 HK dollars; Bank of
East Asia jumped 4.55 percent to 16.10 HK dollars; and Dao Heng
Bank rose 4.99 percent to 35.80 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Depressing the market was HSI benchmark China Telecom, which
fell 3.79 percent to 63.50 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 12.784 billion HK dollars (1.639 billion US
dollars), compared with Monday's 14.658 billion HK dollars (1.879
billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Of the four sub-indices of Hang Seng Index, Finance, Utilities
and Properties gained 3.23 percent, 0.39 percent and 0.94 percent,
respectively, while Commerce and Industry lost 1.40 percent.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-
Affiliated Corp Index gained 2.59 percent and 3.80 percent,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index lost 2.47 percent and the Hang Seng IT
Portfolio Index 0.13 percent.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong stocks went down 78.81 points, or 0.50 percent, to
open at 15,782.87 Wednesday and closed the morning session at 15,
907.65. 
</P>
</TEXT>
