<HEADLINE> China Satisfied with Relations with Myanmar: Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin today
voiced satisfaction over relations between China and Myanmar,
stressing the two countries should join hands to safeguard their
own interest as well peace, stability and prosperity in the region.
</P>
<P>
China and Myanmar, as close neighbors and developing countries,
are faced with the common task of safeguarding peace, developing
economy, and upgrading people's living standards, Jiang said
during a meeting with Maung Aye, vice-chairman of the State Peace
and Development Council of Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The president said Maung Aye's current visit, which coincides
with the 50th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties,
demonstrates the importance the Myanmese government places on
relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
In the past half a century, bilateral relations have withstood
tests. Through the efforts of both sides considerable progress has
been made, the president said. He expressed the belief Maung Aye's
current visit will contribute to the further advancement of
relations, citing the successful talks between Maung Aye and Vice-
President Hu Jintao and a joint statement issued yesterday.
</P>
