<HEADLINE> CTBT Validity Not Whether But When: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The entry of the Comprehensive
Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty (CTBT) into force is just a matter of time,
Executive Secretary Wolfgang Hoffmann of the Preparatory
Commission of the Comprehensive Nuclear-Test-Ban Treaty
Organization (CTBTO) said today.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident that the question is not whether but when we
will have entry into force," said Hoffmann at the Regional
Workshop for the CTBTO International Cooperation and National
Implementation/Ratification Procedures.
</P>
<P>
He said he was encouraged by the willingness of states in the
region to work together to resolve difficulties associated with
the development of national legislation to implement the CTBT.
"This is an essential step toward achieving the goal of
universality and entry into force," he said.
</P>
<P>
Praising the workshop as a "useful forum" to exchange views on
possible benefits of CTBT participation and in promoting dialog in
developing a framework for future cooperation, he said that the
discussions in the workshop have shown the potential for
cooperation in the area of the implementation.
</P>
<P>
Hoffmann said the preparatory commission is doing its best to
promote an early entry into force. He also praised the host's
efforts to arrange the three-day gathering.
</P>
<P>
During Hoffmann's stay in Beijing, Chinese Vice Foreign
Minister Wang Guangya met with him. Director Sha Zukang of the
Department of Arms Control and Disarmament of China's Foreign
Ministry also held talks with Hoffmann. 
</P>
</TEXT>
