<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Stocks Succumb to Profit-taking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Philippine stocks snapped from a
three-day rise Wednesday after investors embarked on profit-taking
on some blue-chip stocks.
</P>
<P>
The 30-company Phisix, the market's main index, fell 40.05
points, or 2.56 percent, to close at 1522.23. The broader all-
shares index was also lower by 11.54 points to 642.26.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said investors cashed in on recent gains on
expectations the market rebound was overdone.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 1.3 billion shares worth some 20 million U.S.
dollars on Wednesday against Tuesday's 2.2 billion shares worth
some 31 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
