<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympic Medals Struck at Mint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The medals to be awarded to the
Olympic champions at the Sydney Games were officially struck at
the Royal Australian Mint on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The medal features the image of the Sydney Opera House, the
Olympic Torch, Olympic Rings and a Greek goddess.  "It combines
the traditional elements that are supposed to be on the medal in a
slightly different form," the designer, Wojciech Pietranik said.
</P>
<P>
The Royal Australian Mint will be responsible for striking the
silver and bronze medals while the gold medals will be made by the
Perth Mint in Western Australia.
</P>
<P>
There will be about 300 medal ceremonies for Olympic finals at
the Sydney Games starting on September 15. 
</P>
</TEXT>
