<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Meets Moldova President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor Liu Qi met with
visiting Moldova President Petru Lucinschi here today.
</P>
<P>
Liu extended a warm welcome to Lucinschi, saying that bilateral
relations have witnessed smooth growth since the forging of
diplomatic ties between the two countries in 1992.
</P>
<P>
He said Beijing and the capital city of Moldova Chisinau share
many things in common, and are faced with similar problems in
their development. Beijing is willing to increase exchanges with
Chisinau and carry out cooperation in different fields, he said,
expressing his belief that President Lucinschi's current visit
will help promote cooperation between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
Lucinschi voiced his support for and confidence in cooperation
between the two cities in education, culture, art, science and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the meeting, Liu and mayor of Chisinau Serafim
Urechean signed a memorandum on cooperation between the two cities.
</P>
<P>
Lucinschi arrived in Beijing earlier today for a 6-day state
visit at the invitation of Chinese President Jiang Zemin. 
</P>
