<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 1st Lead: Sri Lankan Minister Killed in Suicide Bomb Attack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Senior Sri Lankan Minister of
Industrial Development C. V. Gunaratne was killed Wednesday
afternoon in a suicide bombing carried out by suspected Tamil
Tiger rebels.
</P>
<P>
Police said the bombing happened at 1:45 p.m. (0745 GMT) at
Ratmalana in southern suburb of Colombo when the minister was
leading a procession in his electorate to commemorate the War
Heroes Day which fell on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Initial reports said Mayor of Dehiwala-Mt.Lavinia Jayaratne
Perera and at least seven others have also been killed in the
bombing.
</P>
<P>
Number of casualties are not known yet and the police have
moved to the scene of attack.
</P>
<P>
Gunaratne was seen this morning with President Kumaratunga at
the main ceremony held at the President's Secretariat to mark the
War Heroes Day.
</P>
<P>
The minister was a popular figure who moved with the masses
freely and this attack has come in the wake of President
Kumaratunga's tough warning this morning to the Liberation Tigers
of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels, who have been fighting for 17 years to carve
out a homeland for minority Tamils, are known for setting off
explosions to assassinate government officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
