<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solomon Militia Uses Australian Patrol Boat in War </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Solomon's Rebel fighters used
a seized Australian-supplied patrol boat to shell rivals Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Australian Associated Press, Guerrillas from
the Malaitan Eagle Force (MEF) fired rounds from the boat's 50mm
cannon onto shore blowing up an unoccupied school. 50 to 100
members of the opposing Isatabu Freedom Movement (IFM) died
allegedly in the attack.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fighting intensified around the nation's international
airport as the two groups struggled to gain the upper hand
following Monday's attempted coup against the government.
</P>
<P>
The boat, called the Lata, is one of two that Australia donated
to the Solomon Islands in the 1980s for fisheries enforcement and
surveillance.
</P>
<P>
A Red Cross spokesman said it was too early to say how many
casualties there were. 
</P>
</TEXT>
