<HEADLINE> China Strives to Provide Better Social Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has taken a
series of measures in recent years to ensure that the basic rights
and benefits of laborers be guaranteed, a Chinese official said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the on-going International Labor Conference, China'
s Labor Minister Zhang Zuoji told a plenum that China has now
established a three-layer social security program with Chinese
characteristics, which will ensure basic livelihood and
unemployment insurance for laid off workers and minimum living
standards for urban residents.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Zhang said, China has implemented a re-
employment project to help laid off workers get new jobs.
</P>
<P>
China is also speeding up reforms of the social security
systems in pension, unemployment and medical services and has
established certain systems that suit the national conditions of
China, Zhang added.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the Chinese government is willing to
strengthen its cooperation with the International Labor
Organization and all of its members, to share and use for
reference their experience in improving the construction of labor
markets and the establishment of social security systems, in order
to jointly promote the development of the world labor insurance.
</P>
