<HEADLINE> Russia to Invest in Angolan Dam Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Russian diamond enterprise Almazy
Alrosa- Sakha will soon invest some 40 million U.S. dollars in the
construction of a dam over the Chicapa River in Angola's eastern
Lunda-sul province.
</P>
<P>
The state-owned newspaper Jornal de Angola quoted the deputy
president of the company Serguei Oulin as saying that the dam will
serve the Catoca diamond mining project, the largest of its kind
in Angola and the potential fourth largest in the world that is
located in the Lunda-sul province.
</P>
<P>
Serguei Oulin is visiting the diamond-rich southwest African
country for talks with the Angolan authorities on the issue of the
geologic and mineral sectors.
</P>
<P>
The building of the Chicapa dam will serve not only power
supply to the mineral projects but also the population, he said
after meeting geology and mining deputy minister, Carlos Sumbula.
