<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angola Telecom to Spend $3 Million on Phone Project in Huambo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Angola Telecom will spend some three
million U.S. dollars to repair and expand telephone network in the
war-ravaged central province of Huambo, the official news agency
Angop reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The projects include expanding the telephone network of the
Caala city and refurbishing the cable network in Huambo, as well
as purchasing computers.
</P>
<P>
With these done, the Huambo telephone station will have its
clients increase from 1,600 to 10,000.
</P>
<P>
Over-26-year civil war between the government troops and the
rebels led by Jonas Savimbi has destroyed most infrastructures in
the central region of Angola, with the cable cut and the telephone
network paralyzed.
</P>
<P>
The government troops recovered most cities and towns in the
region in an all-out offensive later last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
