<HEADLINE> U.S., DPRK Resume Talks on Missing American Soldiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The United States and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) resumed talks here
Wednesday on looking for American soldiers missing in the Korean
War.
</P>
<P>
"The primary goal of these talks is to renew bilateral
discussions with the Korean People's Army to achieve the fullest
possible accounting of American servicemen," a statement issued by
the U.S. embassy said.
</P>
<P>
The American team from the U.S. Defense Department would seek
to reach agreement on conducting a single, expanded joint recovery
operation in areas where the DPRK claimed to have disinterred four
or five remains of U.S. soldiers, it said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S.-DPRK talks here will be going on until June 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
