<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-German Engine Maintenance Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China Southern Airlines (CSA)
announced it will cooperate with MTU, a German engine
manufacturing giant, in building a service center for engine
maintenance.
</P>
<P>
The contract was signed in Zhuhai City, Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The new joint venture is located inside the bonded zone of
Zhuhai City. It will cover an area of 160,000 sq m.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will cost 180 million U.S. dollars which will
be shared by both investors. The project is expected to be
completed and put in service by 2002.
</P>
<P>
By 2006, the joint venture will gain a capacity of servicing
150 sets of aircraft engines annually.
</P>
<P>
MTU is a leading engine maker in Germany. It operates three
subsidiaries engaged in the maintenance of civilian engines. MTU
earned 1.7 billion Euro in business turnovers in 1999.
</P>
<P>
CSA has grown into one of China's leading airlines.  
</P>
</TEXT>
