<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Kills 38 in SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rain that hit central
Sichuan Province in southwest China since June has killed 38
people. Twelve are still missing.
</P>
<P>
The torrential rain, accompanied by occasional hailstones,
caused flooding, mudslide and landslide in Gulin and Xuyong
counties in central Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
Gulin County suffered the worst losses. Twenty-six people were
killed and six are reported still missing. Some 800 meters of road
was destroyed by landslide.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has launched disaster-relief efforts
to help flooding victims. 
</P>
</TEXT>
