<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing to Do Ten More Good Things For Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) --The Beijing municipal government
will do ten more good deeds for the disabled this year, according
to Beijing vice-mayor Zhai Hongxiang recently.
</P>
<P>
This year's ten good things include providing free medical
facilities to 200 grassroots recovery centers, training for the
disabled so as to help them find jobs, distributing 3 million yuan
(370,000 US dollars) of poverty-relief loans for the handicapped
in rural areas and setting up an employment service center for the
disabled.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has a total of 460,000 handicapped, 4.5 percent of the
total population. Since 1990, the municipal government has done 10
good things for the handicapped every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
