<HEADLINE> Anniversary of Sino-Myanmese Relations Observed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A reception was held here today to
mark the 50th anniversary of the establishment of Sino-Myanmese
diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
Maung Aye, visiting Vice-Chairman of the State Peace and
Development Council of Myanmar, and He Luli, Vice-Chairwoman of
China's National People's Congress Standing Committee, attended
the reception which was hosted by the Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC).
</P>
<P>
Chen Haosu, Vice-President of CPAFFC, said at the reception
that recent years have witnessed a smooth development of bilateral
ties in politics, economy, trade, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
The frequent exchanges of high-level visits has promoted the
understanding and trust between the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Chen said that furthering good-neighborly friendship between
the two countries is not only in the interest of the two peoples,
but conducive to peace and stability in Asia and the rest of the
world.
</P>
<P>
Myanmese Ambassador to China U Ba Htay Chit expressed his
confidence that bilateral friendly ties established by the elder
generation of the two countries will be further promoted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
