<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Daily Report on Quality of Air in Key Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Taiyuan and Xi'an in northwestern
China suffered slight air pollution today, while Beijing, Tianjin,
Shijiazhuang, Shenyang, Yantai and Guiyang had extremely slight
air pollution.
</P>
<P>
The report, issued by the China Environmental Monitoring Center,
said that Hohhot, Dalian, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing, Suzhou,
Nantong, Hangzhou, Wenzhou, Hefei, Fuzhou, Nanchang, Jinan,
Qingdao, Zhengzhou, Wuhan, Guangzhou, Shantou, Chongqing, Chengdu,
Lhasa, Lanzhou, Xining and Urumqi enjoyed fairly good air.
</P>
<P>
Excellent air was reported in Changchun, Xiamen, Shangsha,
Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Zhanjiang, Nanning, Haikou, Kunming and Yinchuan,
all in the south and the southwest.
</P>
<P>
Beijing, Tianjin, Shenyang, Dalian, Harbin, Shanghai, Nanjing,
Suzhou, Hangzhou, Xi'an, and 20 other cities listed absorbable
suspended particles as the major pollutants, while sulfur dioxide
was the major pollutant in Guiyang and Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The 42 cities include China's four municipalities directly
under the central government, the provincial and regional capitals
and 10 key coastal cities.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
