<HEADLINE> Kenyan Youth Complain of Selfish Politicians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of young people have
complained to Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi that a majority of
elected leaders were only pursuing selfish interests.
</P>
<P>
Moi stopped in the street of the capital Nairobi on his way to
office and listened carefully to them on Tuesday, Kenyan
newspapers reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Although politicians claimed to yearn for advice during the
current difficult economic times, most politicians avoid people
to concentrate merely on their personal matters, young people
asserted.
</P>
<P>
Moi said that it was wrong for a section of the opposition to
preach against resumption of aid to Kenya and it was this
heartless attitude that had stalled economic growth and creation
of more jobs.
</P>
<P>
The president emphasized the need for unity among all Kenyans
in tackling the country's problems.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, a motion was passed in parliament to equip
parliamentarians with guns after lawmakers from the ruling party
and opposition took a common stand.
</P>
<P>
The passage has drawn massive criticism from Kenyans since
insecurity poses a menace to all Kenyans, not just lawmakers.
</P>
