<HEADLINE> China's First Securities WAP Website Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- China has started its first
securities WAP (wireless application protocol) website in Beijing:
www.158china.com.
</P>
<P>
The wireless website -- wap.158china.com -- now provides WAP
cellular phone users access to financial news, instant stock
quotes, commentary and stock market advice.
</P>
<P>
Website spokesman, Liang Yonggang, said in about one month,
online stock trading services would be opened simultaneously on
www.158china.com and the wireless wap.158china.com.
</P>
<P>
The website also aims to provide customized services. Leading
web portals in China, including www.sina.com.cn and www.sohu.com
have recently opened their WAP websites.
</P>
<P>
Though China's WAP mobile phone users are currently very
limited, industrial sources said the potential for mobile Internet
services is very big in China.  
</P>
</TEXT>
