<HEADLINE> Chinese Military To Have Lawyers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese military will have
their own lawyers under a recent decision by the Central Military
Commission, according to today's "Legal Daily".
</P>
<P>
Army commanders, divisions and brigades will have lawyers so as
to meet the needs of military construction in the socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that lawyers will became part of China's
military. China's military has already set up over 270 legal
consultant offices employing more than 1,700 military lawyers.
