<HEADLINE> Jordan Asks for Saudi Help to Track Bank Embezzler </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian police are asking their
Saudi Arabian counterparts to help track down and expatriate a
Jordanian citizen who stole some 250,000 Jordanian dinars (350,000
U.S. dollars) from a bank in southern Jordan.
</P>
<P>
The man, identified only as M.S., drew cash at random from
several clients' accounts at the Housing Bank's Qasr branch office
at the Karak district from January to May this year, the
semiofficial daily Jordan Times reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The headquarters of the Housing Bank in Amman found the
discrepancies in the accounts, and alerted the Qasr branch, but the
suspect was believed to have left the kingdom and entered Saudi
Arabia, Jordan Times said.
</P>
<P>
The Housing Bank is the largest of the 23 commercial banks based
in the kingdom in terms of capital.  
</P>
</TEXT>
