after being told by European Union (EU) emissaries in Honiara that
the EU would cancel all aid to a Solomon Islands ruled by
unconstitutional means.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, Sasako also said negotiations between the rebel
Malaita Eagle Force (MEF), for which Nori worked, and the
government caucus regarding security and political stability were
continuing.
</P>
<P>
Both sides of the current political upheaval were "mindful of
the views and counsel of the international community," Sasako said.
