<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Drops in Euro Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate fell to 9.2
percent in the euro zone in April, a 0.1 percent reduction over
March, the European Statistics Bureau Eurostat announced Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat said the jobless reached 12 million in the zone in
April, 1 million less than the figure a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment in the 15 European Union (EU) countries decreased
from 8.6 percent in March to 8.5 percent in April. The figure was
9.3 percent in EU countries one year ago. The bureau estimated
that unemployment totaled 14.6 million people in the EU in April.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate for women in the euro zone hit 11.4 percent,
3.7 percentage points more than for men. About 17.2 percent of
people under 25 lost their jobs. The figure for people under 25
exceeded 20 percent in Belgium, France, Spain and Finland.
</P>
</TEXT>
