<HEADLINE> WHO to Promote Health in 3 Fields </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 6 (Xinhua) -- The World Health Organization (
WHO) has restructured its health promotion programs to fit into
three fundamental fields -- health promotion, aging and mental
health, and non-contagious illnesses, a WHO official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The objectives are to prevent and control non-contagious
sicknesses, including psychic alterations and violence, said
Alexandre Kalache, acting director of WHO's Health Promotion
Department, at the Fifth World Conference of Health Promotion.
</P>
<P>
The 10 main causes of mortality and morbidity at world level
include heart ailments, depression, accidents, brain illnesses,
lung obstructing disorders and lesions, the official said.
</P>
<P>
Over 60 ministers and 100 delegations are participating in the
WHO conference, which will end on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Kalache also voiced support for governments adopting measures
to improve the quality of life. 
</P>
