<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Flood Kills 36 In NW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Devastating floods in the counties
of Dangchang and Minxian in northwest China's Gansu Province on
May 31 killed 36 persons and left thousands homeless.
</P>
<P>
The worst flooding in 150 years destroyed 1,345 houses and
affected 180,000 people in the two counties, 400 km from the
provincial capital of Lanzhou, according to sources from the
provincial disaster-relief working group.
</P>
<P>
Direct economic losses were estimated at 178 million yuan (21.
45 million US dollars),
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has mobilized 5 million yuan (602,400
dollars), 800 quilts, 10,000 clothes, 120 tents and other disaster-
relief materials for flooding victims.
</P>
<P>
No cases of epidemic diseases have been reported in the
flooding area thus far. 
</P>
</TEXT>
