<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Firms, Big Economic Generator in Zhejiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Private businesses have been
making increasing contributions to economic growth in east China's
Zhejiang Province, which ranks the fourth in China in terms GDP.
</P>
<P>
By March, there were 153,000 private companies. Local private
firms generated 399.4 billion yuan in industrial output value last
year, up 25.87 percent on a yearly basis, and dealt with 23.32
billion yuan worth of exports, up 116.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Local private businesses are engaged in a wide range of areas
from knitting, garments, toys, farm products, machinery,
electronics to chemicals, household appliance and auto parts.
</P>
<P>
The province now has 13 private enterprises with more than 100
million yuan of assets each. Thirty-six have an annual output
value exceeding 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Local private firms have patented more than 13,000 trade marks,
34 of which are known nationwide. 
</P>
</TEXT>
