<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sichuan's Investment Fair Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Sichuan Province in southwest China
signed 98 cooperative agreements worth 13.76 billion yuan with
domestic and foreign businessmen during a recent Investment Fair.
</P>
<P>
The agreements cover transportation, urban construction,
environmental protection, building material, medicine, agriculture,
tourism and real estate.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 enterprises from the United States, Britain,
France, Italy, Japan, and other countries and regions, and from 16
provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities of China attended
the five-day Investment Fair held in Chengdu, the capital of
Sichuan Province in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Products on display at 1,200 booths included light industry,
chemicals, agriculture, electronics, telecommunications, and
machinery products.
</P>
<P>
An international forum on the development of western China was
also held during the Fair, sponsored by the China Council for the
Promotion of International Trade, the China Chamber of
International Commerce, and governments from Sichuan province and
the city of Shenzhen in Guangzhou province. 
</P>
