<HEADLINE> Strong Quake Hits Central Japan Facing Japan Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 5.8 on
the open-ended Richter scale jolted wide areas in central Japan
facing the Sea of Japan early Wednesday morning, the
Meteorological Agency said.
</P>
<P>
There were no immediate reports of damage and casualties, and
no tsunami or tidal wave warning was issued.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake, which struck at around 6:16 a.m. (
local time), was estimated to be some 10 kilometers deep in the
Sea of Japan west of Ishikawa Prefecture, the agency said.
</P>
