<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, June 7 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- Britain on Tuesday called for a ban on the export of
diamonds from rebel-held areas of Sierra Leone.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Secretary Robin Cook told the House of Commons that
Britain is pressing for an international trade embargo on diamonds
from Sierra Leone, a former British colony.
</P>
<P>
He said the trade in diamonds in Sierra Leone is fueling the
civil war in that Western African nation. (Britain-S.Leone-
Diamonds)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy favors the idea advanced by Russian President
Vladimir Putin here Monday of developing an anti-missile system
with European countries and NATO, Italian Foreign Minister
Lamberto Dini said Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
"We can only look with favor" on the proposal, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the annual gala evening of the Italo-American
Association NIAF, Dini remarked that Putin already proposed
developing an anti-missile system with the United States, in talks
with U.S. President Bill Clinton. (Italy-Russia-Missile)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France will cut short its presidential term from seven
years to five years in a major reform of the Constitution of the
Fifth Republic drafted under General Charles de Gaulle.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac said Monday evening that he
approves a reform which shortens the office of the president by
two years but does not restrict the number of terms to be served
by a French citizen elected president. (France-Presidential Term-
Chirac)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat and Israeli Prime
Minister Ehud Barak held talks in the West Bank city of Ramallah
Tuesday evening on the final-stage Israeli withdrawal. (Palestine-
Israel-Talks)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greek Economy and Finance Minister Yiannos
Papantoniou said Tuesday that Greece would participate in the
European Union's core for the first time because the country had
won the battle for growth and low inflation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in Athens, just a day after an
EU finance ministers' decision to approve Greece's Economic and
Monetary Union (EMU) membership, Papantoniou said that this was
the last step before a formal approval at an EU summit in Lisbon,
Portugal on June 19.  (Greece-Euro Zone)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Philippine government refuted Tuesday a top
Muslim leader's accusation that the government failed to fulfill
the provisions of the peace agreement it signed with the Moro
National Liberation Front (MNLF) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora told reporters that 23.7
billion pesos (593 million U.S. dollars) worth of projects aimed
at transforming Mindanao into a food basket had been unveiled
during President Joseph Estrada's visit to the island three months
ago. (Philippines-Muslim Leader)  
</P>
