<HEADLINE> France Beats Morocco to Clinch King Cup Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RABAT, June 6 (Xinhua) -- World champions France sharpened
their scoring skills with a 5-1 win over Morocco in Casablanca,
Morocco on Tuesday, just five days before the start of the
European soccer championship finals.
</P>
<P>
The French team clinched the King Hassan II Cup crown for the
second time in a row after winning the tournament on the eve of
their World Cup success in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal's Thierry Henry gave France the lead in the 26th minute,
slotting home after getting a fine pass from Nicolas Anelka.
</P>
<P>
After the interval, midfielder Youri Djorkaeff converted from
the penalty spot in the 56th.
</P>
<P>
The hosts Morocco then pulled a goal back with a header by
Talal El Kharkouri ten minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Christophe Dugarry scored 15 minutes from time after a fine
pass from Zinedine Zidane, who replaced Djorkaeff.
</P>
<P>
Anelka netted the French team's fourth goal in the 84th before
substitute Sylvain Wiltord scored France's fifth in the final
minute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
