<HEADLINE> Tianjin Becomes Trial City for E-commerce </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 7 (Xinhua) -- North China's Tianjin Municipality
has been selected by the State information office as a trial city
to experiment with e-commerce.
</P>
<P>
Tianjin has come up with a general e-commerce outline selecting
a number of enterprises and popularizing the use of Internet in
all its business sectors.
</P>
<P>
The next stage will be for the city to develop e-commerce by
launching a networking project among finance, taxation and trade
sectors, and begin a trial operation of its e-commerce network.
</P>
<P>
An industrial Internet website has been set up attracting more
than 500 local enterprises. The city has also launched a special
training program to promote e-commerce.  
