<HEADLINE> Tourism Reinforced in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The coastal Zhejiang province in
east China will further develop and promote its tourism industry,
said Wang Yongming, vice-governor of the province at a symposium
recently.
</P>
<P>
The province made 40.9 billion yuan (4.9 billion US dollars)
from tourism last year, accounting for 7.3 percent of its gross
domestic product (GDP).
</P>
<P>
Wang said that more and more people have brief getaways on the
weekends and holidays, offering big business opportunities for the
tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The province is also targeting people from overseas. In 1999,
about 948,000 overseas tourists traveled around the province,
generating 410 million US dollars. The provincial government will
further improve shopping, accommodation and transportation
facilities to meet the increasing needs of tourism, Wang noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
