<HEADLINE> Gougot Wins Second Stage of Dauphine-Libere Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 6 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Fabrice Gougot won the 210-
kilometer second stage of the Dauphine-Libere cycling race between
Chatillon/Chalaronne and St Etienne on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Gougot, second to compatriot Frederic Guesdon in Monday's stage,
dedicated the win in his native Saint-Etienne to daughter Priscila,
born a month ago.
</P>
<P>
He beat German team mate Jens Voigt into second place, 13
seconds behind him with Spain's Cesar Solaun a further seven
seconds back with the rest of the pack.
</P>
<P>
Spain's Alberto Lopez de Munain, who won Sunday's time trial,
led the overall standings with a total time of nine hours 48
minutes and seven seconds, 17 seconds ahead of compatriot Jose-
Maria Jimenez. 
</P>
