<HEADLINE> Romania Increases Exports to Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Romania's exports to the area of
Asia-Oceania increased by 11.3 percent in 1999 as against the
previous year, amounting to over one billion U.S. dollars, the
local daily Curentul reported Wednesday, quoting State
Undersecretary in the Ministry of Industry and Commerce Mihai
Berinde.
</P>
<P>
The biggest increases were registered last year in the exports
to Thailand, the Philippines and Pakistan. The daily stressed that
the increase in exports to these areas is relevant, taking into
account the financial crisis in that part of the world in the last
two years.
</P>
<P>
In the year 2000, Romania wants to further develop the
commercial relations with China, to strengthen the partnership
agreement with Japan and to intensify the cooperation with all the
countries in the Asia-Pacific area, Mihai Berinde said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the implementation of this strategy has already
borne fruit: for the first four months of this year, Romania's
exports to this area increased by 18.5 percent as against the same
span of time in 1999 .The most important increase has been
registered in the commercial exchanges with China, South Korea,
Japan, Pakistan and Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
The daily also said that Romania's imports from this area of
the world are about four times bigger than the exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
