<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Seizes 4,400 Bullets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- A total of 4,400 bullets of
different calibers were found by Colombian authorities, official
sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ammunition, hidden in a cargo of corn flour donated to the
victims of the rains in the northeastern department of Norte de
Santander, was discovered by the mayor of the El Carmen village,
Jorge Ortega, to whom one of the 120 corn flour bags, which had
been confiscated to smugglers and sent to the rain victims, broke
accidentally.
</P>
<P>
The municipal official explained that the commodity, which
arrived illegally from Venezuela, was confiscated on March 15
together with automotive parts, and donated to the victims of the
rains by the Norte de Santander department government.
</P>
<P>
The corn flour cargo was given to the El Carmen residents
together with more than 20 boxes of shampoo, canned sardines, and
toothpaste, said Ortega, adding that the group of criminals who
were supposed to receive the ammunition was not identified.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
