<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-07 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuadoran Shrimp Industry Imperiled by White Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The Ecuadoran shrimp industry has a
serious problem with the increase of mortality in the nursery
ponds for this crustacean caused by two viruses and the effects of
the economic crisis in the country, National Aquaculture Chamber
sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The "El Comercio" newspaper said that while in December of 1999
the mortality in the ponds was 70 percent, now it nears 90 percent
because of the white spot.
</P>
<P>
But shrimp production is also affected now by the yellow head
virus, said Sandro Coglitore, Aquaculture Chamber chairman.
</P>
<P>
The shrimp industry sector estimates having lost 660 million
dollars during the last year because of the white spot.
</P>
<P>
Central Bank statistics show that income from shrimp exports
between January and March of this year was 48.6 million U.S.
dollars, compared with 186.1 million dollars in the same period of
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
