<HEADLINE> Brazilian President Grants Interview On-Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian President Fernando
Henrique Cardoso granted Wednesday his first on-line interview,
highlighting his government social programs.
</P>
<P>
The project was proposed by the Terra Internet portal, which
belongs to the Telefonica Spanish group and by Estadao, the
Brazilian newspaper "O Estado de Sao Paulo" portal.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian president was directly interviewed in the Palace
of Alvorada, his official residence in Brasilia, by a group of
journalists of the two firms.
</P>
<P>
All the internauts were able to access the Terra page to
observe the answers of the president, but had no opportunity to
make on line questions.
</P>
<P>
Terra said that the portal users had sent in the last days more
than 8.000 questions to President Cardos. Some of them, mainly
about unemployment, violence, and corruption, were selected as
themes for the interview.
</P>
<P>
U.S. President Bill Clinton took part in an on-line chat in
February of this year, open for all the internauts, through the
television CNN network page. 
</P>
</TEXT>
