<HEADLINE> Spanish Foreign Investments Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 7 (Xinhua) -- Spanish firms direct investment
abroad reached the record 19.714 billion U.S. dollars, Spanish
Second Vice President and Economy Minister Rodrigo Rato said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Rato said that these investments are 5.4 percent of Spain's
gross domestic product (GDP), and that the Spanish firms invested
abroad in 1995 an amount equivalent to 0.5 of the GDP.
</P>
<P>
Spain became last year the second source of foreign investment
in Latin America, after the United States, and directed to that
zone 63 percent of its investments abroad, said Rato. 
</P>
</TEXT>
