<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 7 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. stocks ended higher
Wednesday as a Wall Street analyst gave a rosy prospect for IBM's
earnings, distracting investors from their concerns about
Microsoft's breakup case.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed up 77.29 at 10,812.86
and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index rose 82.89 at 3,
839.26. Both indexes recovered from their decline earlier in the
session.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also higher. The Standard &AMP; Poor'
s 500 index rose 13.52 at 1,471.36.
</P>
<P>
Stocks rallied after Goldman Sachs analyst Laura Conigliaro
said orders to IBM were strong in the past two months and
investors may be undervaluing the stock of the company.
</P>
<P>
The robust estimate distracted investors from their worries
about Microsoft. After the close of session Wednesday, U.S.
District Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson was expected to issue the
final ruling on whether to break the company.
</P>
<P>
Smaller technology companies and biotechnology stocks also
helped the market's advance. Microstrategy, a software maker, rose
sharply as investors anticipated that the company will receive
financing from an outside source.
</P>
<P>
Immunes, a biotechnology company, also rose after the U.S. Food
and Drug Administration expanded its approval of the company's
Enbrel rheumatoid arthritis drug to more patients.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index rose 2.88 at 655.88 and the American Stock
Exchange index rose 6.78 at 934.96. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies rose 4.89 at 516.54.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 6-to-5 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with 1,604 up, 1,323 down and 493
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume declined to 840.19 million shares from 936.15
million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
